ACCOUNTED FOR 5.2 POINTS AND 2.1 POINTS OF THE 2010 AND 2009 LOSS AND LOSS ADJUSTMENT EXPENSE RATIOS, RESPECTIVELY. NET FAVORABLE PRIOR YEAR RESERVE DEVELOPMENT PROVIDED 5.8 POINTS AND 6.2 POINTS OF

BENEFIT TO THE CONSOLIDATED LOSS AND LOSS ADJUSTMENT EXPENSE RATIO IN 2010 AND 2009, RESPECTIVELY. THE CONSOLIDATED LOSS AND LOSS ADJUSTMENT EXPENSE RATIO EXCLUDING CATASTROPHE LOSSES AND PRIOR YEAR

RESERVE DEVELOPMENT IN 2010 WAS 0.2 POINTS HIGHER THAN THE 2009 RATIO ON THE SAME BASIS, PRIMARILY REFLECTING THE IMPACT OF LOSS COST TRENDS.

