COMPARED WITH 2010 REFLECTED GROWTH IN EARNED PREMIUMS AND INCREASES IN COSTS ASSOCIATED WITH THE COMPANY'S DIRECT TO CONSUMER INITIATIVE, THE IMPACTS OF WHICH WERE LARGELY OFFSETTING.

