1. SUMMARY OF SIGNIFICANT ACCOUNTING POLICIES (CONTINUED)

FUND

AND OTHER INSURANCE-RELATED ASSESSMENTS AND RELATED RECOVERABLES OF $19 MILLION AND $24 MILLION, RESPECTIVELY. THE LIABILITY FOR SUCH ASSESSMENTS AND THE RELATED RECOVERABLES ARE

NOT DISCOUNTED FOR THE TIME VALUE OF MONEY. THE LOSS-BASED ASSESSMENTS ARE EXPECTED TO BE PAID OVER A PERIOD RANGING FROM ONE YEAR TO THE LIFE EXPECTANCY OF CERTAIN WORKERS' COMPENSATION

CLAIMANTS AND THE RECOVERIES ARE EXPECTED TO OCCUR OVER THE SAME PERIOD OF TIME.

ALSO

