COMPANY HAS DISCRETION REGARDING WHETHER TO PROVIDE ADDITIONAL FUNDING AND WHEN TO PROVIDE SUCH FUNDING TO ITS QUALIFIED PENSION PLAN. IN 2011 AND 2010, THE COMPANY VOLUNTARILY MADE

CONTRIBUTIONS TOTALING $185 MILLION AND $35 MILLION, RESPECTIVELY, TO THE QUALIFIED PENSION PLAN. THE COMPANY HAS NOT DETERMINED WHETHER OR NOT ADDITIONAL FUNDING WILL BE MADE DURING

2012. THERE IS NO REQUIRED CONTRIBUTION TO THE QUALIFIED PENSION PLAN DURING 2012.

